reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great sturdy rack!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this rack not to hold shoes but to hold all my sodas, Gatorade and other drinks. It is very strong and sturdy to accommodate the weight of all my drinks. Pretty east to assemble but make sure you look closely at instructions to ensure you have the sides and racks in the right direction. Would easily recommend this rack for shoes but makes a great storage rack for drinks!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid shoe rack..
reviews.reviewText: I was so happy to purchase this. I have six people in my house, so that means many shoes are around. It was very easy to assemble and it looks nice and neat in my closet. It fits a good amount of shoes. I would definitely buy this again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value for money
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is fairly easy to put together. I stacked two racks - not the most sturdy rack but holds up pretty well. Overwell it's a good value for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Why didn't i think of this sooner??
reviews.reviewText: I really like this shoe rack - i love to be organized. It was super easy to assemble, all the screws & holes lined up, no "forcing" parts together. The only unfortunate thing, it really only fits sneakers or low shoes on the bottom 3 rows. If you have ankle boots, they can go on top, anything taller might have to stay on the floor. This is holding 12 pairs of my shoes, I wear women's 9 - 10. For me this works perfect, great price and so far seems sturdy. Good buy! :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a very good shoe rack. It's sturdy and easy to assemble. Be aware that it will hold only 12 pair of men's shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits up to 12 men’s shoes
reviews.reviewText: Nice product. I like that everything can be attached using the tool that is provided. Description said it could fit up to twenty pairs. I wear a men’s size 10 and it only could fit 12 pairs (3 on each rack comfortably). Thankfully I bought two. The instructions were mostly clear but it did take me some time to figure out how to attach the shelves. Fits perfectly in my closet. Overall it’s a good buy. Will most likely buy another for my entry way.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A lot stronger than I expected!
reviews.reviewText: I had been using one of those laundry-room sort of "Closet Maid" type of rolling racks in my hallway closet, knowing that it wouldn't suffice for long. Too awkward, too small to be practical.This thing changed all that. It took about five minutes to assemble (a Philips-head screwdriver is the only tool you need, and they even include one). It really is that easy.The package includes a (screw-in) wall brace, because if you buy TWO of them, they stack perfectly. The brace is for the top section, which would otherwise tip over at that height.What good is it if it's not strong, though? I pulled that "Closet Maid" type thing out, and put this in. Then I filled the racks with shoes that were otherwise all over the doggone place.It is completely SOLID. I grabbed it and shook it, expecting it to wobble or warp, but it did nothing of the sort. Most enthusiastically recommended, especially at this price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Assembly was a bit of a nightmare and I found myself struggling with getting this thing together, but it is a sturdy product. Also, do not expect to fit 20 pairs of shoes on this. I'm a US size 12-13 and I was only able to squeeze 13 pairs on it.
